s. As an example of the\napplicability of our construction, we obtain a new\n$\\tilde{\\Omega}(1/\\epsilon^4)$ sampling lower bound for testing the\nSchatten-$1$ norm with a $\\epsilon n^{1.5}$ gap, extending a result of Balcan,\nLi, Woodruff, and Zhang [SODA'19]. In addition, it yields new sampling lower\nbounds for estimating the Ky-Fan Norm, and the cost of the best rank-$k$\napproximation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 May 2020 17:30:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 1 Jun 2020 14:23:07 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 17 Sep 2020 19:10:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-09-21"}
