eraction, show that $T_{\\rm\neff}$ has a strong dependence on $M_{\\rm env}$, $M_{\\rm core}$ and the core\ncomposition. We find the mass of one of these stripped stars in a binary\nsystem, HD 45166, to be less than its dynamical mass. When a large\nobservational sample of stripped stars becomes available, our results can be\nused to constrain their masses and the physics of binary interaction.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 May 2020 17:56:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-27"}
