als. Further elucidation will be necessary, however,\nespecially of phenylalanine's role in condensate assembly because experiments\non FtoA and YtoF mutants suggest that LLPS-driving phenylalanine interactions\nare significantly weaker than those posited by common statistical potentials.\nProtein-protein electrostatic interactions are modulated by relative\npermittivity, which depends on protein concentration. Analytical theory\nsuggests that this dependence entails enhanced inter-protein interactions in\nthe condensed phase but more favorable protein-solvent interactions in the\ndilute phase. The opposing trends lead to a modest overall impact on LLPS.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 May 2020 03:55:52 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 6 Oct 2020 21:01:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-10"}
